es/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/Dockerfile.picod","time":{"start":1775876441723,"end":1775876441730}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876442949,"sessionID":"ses_28584361cffeH5b0m4JrSVKROR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7c070c001U9jpA2W5ZKQLzk","messageID":"msg_d7a7bede5001SXKa9rIS7vjxM1","sessionID":"ses_28584361cffeH5b0m4JrSVKROR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c616ef8337ad41c381541e4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/.dockerignore"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/.dockerignore</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: .git\n2: .gitignore\n3: test/\n4: testing/\n5: sdk-python/\n6: docs/\n7: coverage.out\n8: .pytest_cache/\n9: .coverage\n10: *.md\n11: !README.md\n\n(End of file - total 11 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".git\n.gitignore\ntest/\ntesting/\nsdk-python/\ndocs/\ncoverage.out\n.pytest_cache/\n.coverage\n*.md\n!README.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docker/.dockerignore","time":{"start":1775876442930,"end":1775876442946}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876444311,"sessionID":"ses_28584361cffeH5b0m4JrSVKROR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7c0bc50018Czkzdy5Rnv0bG","messageID":"msg_d7a7bede5001SXKa9rIS7vjxM1","sessionID":"ses_28584361cffeH5b0m4JrSVKROR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5d70d9e9919d408eb8891e1c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `docker`\n6: - **Language:** Dockerfile\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md` (Requirement: Docker images for core binaries)\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` that builds the Workload Manager binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/workloadmanager` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `apiserver` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go toolchain\n17: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n18: - **WHEN** the first (builder) stage is evaluated\n19: - **THEN** it SHALL use a Go base image (e.g. `golang:1.25-alpine`) and set `CGO_ENABLED=0` in the build environment\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles workloadmanager binary\n22: - **GIVEN** the builder stage has the repository source available\n23: - **WHEN** `go build` runs\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/workloadmanager` and produce a static Linux binary at `/workloadmanager` (or equivalent output path)\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n27: - **GIVEN** the second (runtime) stage in `docker/Dockerfile`\n28: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Binary is copied from builder to runtime\n32: - **GIVEN** both stages exist in `docker/Dockerfile`\n33: - **WHEN** the `COPY --from=builder` instruction is evaluated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL copy the compiled `workloadmanager` binary from the builder stage into the runtime image\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Non-root user apiserver is created\n37: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n38: - **WHEN** the image is built\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL create a user `apiserver` with UID 1000 and set `USER apiserver` as the active user\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n42: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n43: - **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n44: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the workloadmanager binary\n47: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n48: - **WHEN** the container starts\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `workloadmanager` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Router Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n52: \n53: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` that builds the Router binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `router` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles router binary\n56: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n57: - **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n61: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n62: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Non-root user router is created\n66: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n67: - **WHEN** the image is built\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL create a user `router` with UID 1000 and set `USER router` as the active user\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n71: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n72: - **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n73: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the router binary\n76: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n77: - **WHEN** the container starts\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `router` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: PicoD Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n81: \n82: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` that builds the PicoD daemon binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as a non-root user, suitable for execution inside sandbox pods.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles picod binary\n85: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n86: - **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n90: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n91: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n92: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Non-root user is configured\n95: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n96: - **WHEN** the image is built\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL create a non-root user (UID ≥ 1000) and set it as the active user via `USER`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the picod binary\n100: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n101: - **WHEN** the container starts\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `picod` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Build context and reproducibility\n105: \n106: All three Dockerfiles SHALL use the repository root as build context and produce deterministic, minimal images suitable for production deployment.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Build context includes Go module files\n109: - **GIVEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile .` is run from the repository root\n110: - **WHEN** the builder stage resolves dependencies\n111: - **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` SHALL be available for `go mod download` before source code is copied (layer caching optimization)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: No unnecessary files in runtime image\n114: - **GIVEN** a built image from any of the three Dockerfiles\n115: - **WHEN** the image filesystem is inspected\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain Go source code, build caches, or the Go toolchain — only the compiled binary, Alpine base packages, and the non-root user home directory\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Image builds succeed from clean checkout\n119: - **GIVEN** a clean clone of the repository at the correct commit\n120: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t workloadmanager:test .` is executed\n121: - **THEN** the build SHALL complete with exit code 0 and produce a valid image\n122: \n123: ### Requirement: Docker build output integrity\n124: \n125: Each built image SHALL contain a working binary that starts and responds to its health endpoint (where applicable).\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image responds to /health\n128: - **GIVEN** a container running from the Workload Manager image with default configuration\n129: - **WHEN** an HTTP GET request is sent to `http://localhost:8080/health`\n130: - **THEN** the response SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Router image starts without root privileges\n133: - **GIVEN** a container running from the Router image\n134: - **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL be 1000 (the `router` user), not 0 (root)\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: PicoD image starts without root privileges\n138: - **GIVEN** a container running from the PicoD image\n139: - **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL be ≥ 1000 (non-root user), not 0 (root)\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## File Changes\n145: \n146: | Action | File | Description |\n147: |--------|------|-------------|\n148: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `apiserver`) |\n149: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `router`) |\n150: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD daemon (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root user) |\n151: | Create | `docker/.dockerignore` | Exclude `.git`, `test/`, `sdk-python/`, `docs/`, and other non-build artifacts from Docker context |\n\n(End of file - total 151 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `docker`\n- **Language:** Dockerfile\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md` (Requirement: Docker images for core binaries)\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n\nThe system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` that builds the Workload Manager binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/workloadmanager` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `apiserver` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go toolchain\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** the first (builder) stage is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use a Go base image (e.g. `golang:1.25-alpine`) and set `CGO_ENABLED=0` in the build environment\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876444301,"end":1775876444309}}}}
